Executive Profile
Richard J. Hipple  Executive Chairman, Materion CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships64$4,010,629As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Richard J. Hipple, also known as Dick, has been an Executive Chairman of Materion Corporation since March 2017.  Mr. Hipple served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Materion Corporation and its subsidiary Brush Wellman, Inc., since May 02, 2006 until March 2017 and its President since May 2005 until March 03, 2017.  Mr. Hipple served as the Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of Brush Engineered Materials Inc. He served as Chief Operating ... Officer of Materion Corporation from May 2005 to May 02, 2006. He served as the President of Alloy Products- Brush Wellman, Inc. from May 2002 to May 2005. Mr. Hipple joined Brush Wellman in July 2001 and served as its Vice President of Strip Products from July 2001 to May 2002. Prior to Brush, he served as the President of LTV Steel Company. Prior to running LTV's steel business, he held numerous leadership positions in Engineering, Operations, Strategic Planning, Sales and Marketing and Procurement since 1975 at LTV. Mr. Hipple has been a Director of Ferro Corporation since June 28, 2007 and serves as its Lead Director. He has been a Director of Materion Corporation since May 02, 2006. He has been a Director of keyCorp. since May 17, 2012. He serves as a Trustee of Manufacturers Alliance/MAPI, Inc. Mr. Hipple  is a graduate of Drexel University with a Bachelor of Science Degree in Engineering in 1975.Read Full Background




